<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1906-05-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1906-05-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="397" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d397">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to Ambassador <persName type="to">Meyer</persName></hi>.</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1906-05-21"><hi rend="italic">May 21,
                                1906</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Bacon directs Mr. Meyer to urge authorities to identify and punish
                            murderers; also directs him to ask the British consul to take charge of
                            the American interests and the American consulate at Batum. Mr. Bacon
                            states that the British Government has been asked to give
                            permission.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>